cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new approach to language modeling by incorporating behavioral information. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new module to be added to language models, which involves training and optimization. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to language modeling that involves incorporating additional contextual information beyond just the sequence of words. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper draws inspiration from psycholinguistics and considers the role of behavioral context in language use. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper considers the state of the speaker as a potential source of contextual information to be incorporated into language models.
